The paper focuses on person re-identification using deep learning and hashing techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of triplet loss function, which is a popular technique in deep learning for similarity learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the evaluation of efficiency and accuracy, which are important aspects of information retrieval (cs.IR) and security and privacy (cs.CR).
